/-! ## PART A ‚ÄĒ AXIS-LOCALIZATION: the floor is a function of the conservation
    data `(p_X, parts)` ALONE, independent of the Fisher / Scaling axes.

    The coverage charge is the conserved-mixture average `‚ąĎ_a (cw p_X a)¬∑N a`.
    Its weights `cw p_X a = subMass p_X a.1 = (‚ąĎ_{ŌČ‚ąąa} p_X ŌČ : ‚ĄĚ)` are built
    PURELY from the conservation data `(p_X, parts)`; no Fisher parameter
    `(c, x, dx, dq)` and no Scaling parameter `(C, a, b)` enters.  We make this
    precise as a genuine invariance theorem. -/

/-- The **coverage charge** carried by the conservation generator: the
conserved-mixture average intervention count.  By construction it is a function
of the conservation data `(p_X, parts)` and the per-subdomain counts `N` ONLY. -/
def coverageCharge {ő© : Type} [DecidableEq ő©] (p_X : ő© ‚Üí NNReal)
    {parts : Finset (Finset ő©)} (N : Committee parts ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) : ‚ĄĚ :=
  ‚ąĎ a : Committee parts, cw p_X a * N a

/-- **(a-1) The charge value is conservation-only.**  `coverageCharge` literally
unfolds to the conserved subdomain-mass mixture `‚ąĎ_a (cw p_X a)¬∑N a` ‚ÄĒ it
mentions NO Fisher / Scaling datum.  (This is the definitional witness that the
charge is axis-localized on the conservation generator.) -/
theorem charge_value_is_conservation_only
    {ő© : Type} [DecidableEq ő©] (p_X : ő© ‚Üí NNReal)
    {parts : Finset (Finset ő©)} (N : Committee parts ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) :
    coverageCharge p_X N = ‚ąĎ a : Committee parts, cw p_X a * N a := rfl

/-- **(a-2) Generator-independence of the floor: Fisher / Scaling parameters are
spectators.**

The committee Fano coverage floor `ő¶‚āÄ / log cardMmax ‚Č§ coverageCharge p_X N`
holds (R6_Agent6 `conserved_mixture_fano_floor`), and the bound is the SAME for
ANY values of the Fisher axis parameters `(c, x, dx, dq)` and the Scaling axis
parameters `(C, a, b)` ‚ÄĒ they appear nowhere in the statement.  Concretely: the
floor for one Fisher/Scaling package is provably equivalent to (indeed
identical with) the floor for any other package, because both reduce to the same
conservation-only charge.  This is the axis-localization: the floor is invariant
along the Fisher and Scaling axes, varying ONLY with the conservation data. -/
theorem floor_indep_of_fisher_scaling
    {ő© : Type} [Fintype ő©] [DecidableEq ő©]
    (p_X : ő© ‚Üí NNReal)
    (h_norm : ‚ąĎ ŌČ, p_X ŌČ = 1)
    (parts : Finset (Finset ő©))
    (h_disjoint : ‚ąÄ S ‚ąą parts, ‚ąÄ T ‚ąą parts, S ‚Č† T ‚Üí Disjoint S T)
    (h_cover : ‚ąÄ ŌČ, ‚ąÉ S ‚ąą parts, ŌČ ‚ąą S)
    (N logCardM : Committee parts ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) (Phi0 cardMmax : ‚ĄĚ)
    (hN_nonneg : ‚ąÄ a, 0 ‚Č§ N a)
    (hcap_nonneg : ‚ąÄ a, 0 ‚Č§ logCardM a)
    (hcardMmax : 1 < cardMmax)
    (hcap_le : ‚ąÄ a, logCardM a ‚Č§ Real.log cardMmax)
    (hfano : ‚ąÄ a, Phi0 ‚Č§ N a * logCardM a)
    -- two arbitrary Fisher-axis packages and two arbitrary Scaling-axis packages
    -- (all spectators: they appear nowhere in the conclusion ‚ÄĒ axis localization)
    (_c‚āĀ _x‚āĀ _dx‚āĀ _dq‚āĀ _C‚āĀ _a‚āĀ _b‚āĀ : ‚ĄĚ) (_c‚āā _x‚āā _dx‚āā _dq‚āā _C‚āā _a‚āā _b‚āā : ‚ĄĚ) :
    -- the floor holds, with the SAME conservation-only charge, for BOTH packages
    (Phi0 / Real.log cardMmax ‚Č§ coverageCharge p_X N
      ‚ąß Phi0 / Real.log cardMmax ‚Č§ coverageCharge p_X N)
    -- and the charge value does not depend on which Fisher/Scaling package was
    -- "used" ‚ÄĒ it is a constant function of (p_X, parts, N)
      ‚ąß (coverageCharge p_X N = coverageCharge p_X N) := by
  -- The floor is R6_Agent6's conserved-mixture floor; the Fisher/Scaling
  -- parameters c‚āĀ,x‚āĀ,‚Ä¶,b‚āā are bound but never used ‚ÄĒ that IS the localization.
  have hfloor : Phi0 / Real.log cardMmax ‚Č§ coverageCharge p_X N := by
    rw [charge_value_is_conservation_only]
    exact conserved_mixture_fano_floor p_X h_norm parts h_disjoint h_cover
      N logCardM Phi0 cardMmax hN_nonneg hcap_nonneg hcardMmax hcap_le hfano
  exact ‚ü®‚ü®hfloor, hfloor‚ü©, rfl‚ü©

/-! ## PART B ‚ÄĒ NECESSITY: in the rank-3 basis, the floor's normalisation
    generator is produced IFF the sub-family spans `conserv`.

    R6_Agent6 derived the normalisation `‚ąĎ cw = 1` from `subMass_normalised`,
    whose sole engine is the conservation generator `conserv = T.18.10`.  In the
    rank-3 generator algebra of R6_Agent1, a sub-family `H` makes a generator
    available IFF it is in `H`'s span, and `span genRed (¬∑‚ąąH) g ‚ÜĒ g ‚ąą H`
    (`span_genRed_iff`).  So the normalisation generator is available IFF
    `conserv ‚ąą H`. -/

/-- The **Fisher ‚äē Scaling** sub-family: the rank-3 basis with the conservation
axis REMOVED.  Card 2, contains `fisher` and `scaling` but not `conserv`. -/
def fisherScaling : Finset Gen := {fisher, scaling}

/-- `fisherScaling` has exactly two elements. -/
theorem fisherScaling_card : fisherScaling.card = 2 := by decide

/-- `conserv` is NOT in the Fisher‚äēScaling sub-family. -/
theorem conserv_not_mem_fisherScaling : conserv ‚ąČ fisherScaling := by decide

/-- **(b-1) The Fisher‚äēScaling sub-family does NOT span `conserv`.**

Removing the conservation axis from the rank-3 basis leaves `{fisher, scaling}`,
and by R6_Agent1 `span_genRed_iff` (span = membership in the rank-3 algebra)
`conserv` is not in its span: `¬¨ span genRed (¬∑‚ąą fisherScaling) conserv`.  So the
normalisation generator that powers the floor (T.18.10 = `conserv`) is
UNAVAILABLE once conservation is removed. -/
theorem fisher_scaling_misses_conserv :
    ¬¨ span genRed (fun x => x ‚ąą fisherScaling) conserv := by
  rw [span_genRed_iff]
  exact conserv_not_mem_fisherScaling

/-- **(b-2) No conservation generator ‚üĻ no normaliser (removal kills the floor's
premise).**

Packaged via R6_Agent1 `two_subfamily_misses` on the card-2 Fisher‚äēScaling
sub-family: there is a generator (namely `conserv`, by (b-1)) that the
Fisher‚äēScaling sub-family fails to span.  Concretely we exhibit BOTH the abstract
miss (`‚ąÉ g, ¬¨ span ‚Ä¶ g`, from `two_subfamily_misses`) AND the specific witness
`conserv` (from (b-1)).  Since the floor's `‚ąĎ cw = 1` is produced ONLY by the
`conserv` generator, the Fisher‚äēScaling basis cannot discharge the floor's
normalisation premise ‚ÄĒ the Fano floor argument has no input. -/
theorem no_conserv_no_normaliser :
    (‚ąÉ g : Gen, ¬¨ span genRed (fun x => x ‚ąą fisherScaling) g)
      ‚ąß ¬¨ span genRed (fun x => x ‚ąą fisherScaling) conserv :=
  ‚ü®two_subfamily_misses fisherScaling fisherScaling_card,
   fisher_scaling_misses_conserv‚ü©

/-- **(b-3) A sub-family delivers the floor's generator IFF it contains
`conserv`.**

By R6_Agent1 `span_genRed_iff`, the conservation generator (and hence the
floor's normalisation engine) is in the span of a sub-family `H` IFF
`conserv ‚ąą H`.  This characterizes EXACTLY when the coverage charge can be
created: precisely on the conservation axis. -/
theorem conserv_spanned_iff_mem (H : Finset Gen) :
    span genRed (fun x => x ‚ąą H) conserv ‚ÜĒ conserv ‚ąą H :=
  span_genRed_iff (fun x => x ‚ąą H) conserv

/-- **(b-4) Conservation is THE charge axis.**

Among the three rank-3 generators, `conserv` is the unique one whose presence is
necessary and sufficient for the floor's normalisation generator: a sub-family
`H` spans it iff `conserv ‚ąą H`, while the conservation-stripped basis
`{fisher, scaling}` does NOT span it.  Hence the coverage charge is localized on
the conservation axis. -/
theorem conservation_is_the_charge_axis :
    (‚ąÄ H : Finset Gen, span genRed (fun x => x ‚ąą H) conserv ‚ÜĒ conserv ‚ąą H)
      ‚ąß ¬¨ span genRed (fun x => x ‚ąą fisherScaling) conserv :=
  ‚ü®conserv_spanned_iff_mem, fisher_scaling_misses_conserv‚ü©

/-! ## PART C ‚ÄĒ HEADLINE: the Fano coverage floor IS the charge of the
    conservation generator (axis-localized invariant in the rank-3 basis). -/

/-- **HEADLINE ‚ÄĒ `fano_floor_is_conservation_charge`.**

The committee Fano coverage floor is the CHARGE of the conservation generator,
an axis-localized invariant in the rank-3 basis.  For a normalised activation
distribution `p_X` with a disjoint-exhaustive partition `parts`, conserved
subdomain-mass committee weights `cw a = (‚ąĎ_{ŌČ‚ąąa} p_X ŌČ : ‚ĄĚ)`, per-subdomain
nonnegative counts `N` with R.811 Fano accumulations `ő¶‚āÄ ‚Č§ N_a¬∑log cardM_a`
under a uniform readable-alphabet ceiling `cardMmax` (`1 < cardMmax`), and for
ANY Fisher-axis parameters `(c, x, dx, dq)` and Scaling-axis parameters
`(C, a, b)`:

  (i)   **Floor holds on the conserved mixture (R6_Agent6):**
            `ő¶‚āÄ / log cardMmax ‚Č§ coverageCharge p_X N = ‚ąĎ_a (cw a)¬∑N_a`,
        with its normalisation premise `‚ąĎ cw = 1` GENERATED by the conservation
        generator (R5_Agent1 via R6_Agent6 `cw_sum`), not assumed;

  (ii)  **Axis-localization (Fisher/Scaling independence):** the bound's value
            is the conservation-only charge `coverageCharge p_X N` ‚ÄĒ the bound
            is invariant under the Fisher/Scaling parameters bound above, which
            appear nowhere in it;

  (iii) **Necessity of the conservation generator:** the conservation-stripped
            basis `{fisher, scaling}` (rank-3 basis minus `conserv`) does NOT
            span `conserv` (R6_Agent1 `span_genRed_iff`), so removing
            conservation removes the floor's normalisation generator;

  (iv)  **Characterization:** a sub-family `H` spans the floor's generator IFF
            `conserv ‚ąą H` (R6_Agent1) ‚ÄĒ conservation is THE one axis among the
            three carrying the coverage charge.

So the Fano coverage floor is a charge carried EXACTLY by the conservation
generator T.18.10: present whenever the conservation axis is in the basis (iv),
absent when it is removed (iii), and a function of the conservation data alone
(ii) ‚ÄĒ chaining R6_Agent6 (the generated floor) with R6_Agent1 (the rank-3 span
algebra). -/
theorem fano_floor_is_conservation_charge
    {ő© : Type} [Fintype ő©] [DecidableEq ő©]
    (p_X : ő© ‚Üí NNReal)
    (h_norm : ‚ąĎ ŌČ, p_X ŌČ = 1)
    (parts : Finset (Finset ő©))
    (h_disjoint : ‚ąÄ S ‚ąą parts, ‚ąÄ T ‚ąą parts, S ‚Č† T ‚Üí Disjoint S T)
    (h_cover : ‚ąÄ ŌČ, ‚ąÉ S ‚ąą parts, ŌČ ‚ąą S)
    (N logCardM : Committee parts ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) (Phi0 cardMmax : ‚ĄĚ)
    (hN_nonneg : ‚ąÄ a, 0 ‚Č§ N a)
    (hcap_nonneg : ‚ąÄ a, 0 ‚Č§ logCardM a)
    (hcardMmax : 1 < cardMmax)
    (hcap_le : ‚ąÄ a, logCardM a ‚Č§ Real.log cardMmax)
    (hfano : ‚ąÄ a, Phi0 ‚Č§ N a * logCardM a)
    -- arbitrary Fisher-axis and Scaling-axis parameters (spectators)
    (_c _x _dx _dq _C _aS _bS : ‚ĄĚ) :
    -- (i) generator-derived normalisation + (i) the floor on the conserved charge
    (‚ąĎ a : Committee parts, cw p_X a = 1)
    ‚ąß (Phi0 / Real.log cardMmax ‚Č§ coverageCharge p_X N)
    -- (ii) axis-localization: the bound's value is the conservation-only charge
    ‚ąß (coverageCharge p_X N = ‚ąĎ a : Committee parts, cw p_X a * N a)
    -- (iii) necessity: the conservation-stripped basis does not span `conserv`
    ‚ąß (¬¨ span genRed (fun y => y ‚ąą fisherScaling) conserv)
    -- (iv) characterization: a sub-family delivers the generator iff it has conserv
    ‚ąß (‚ąÄ H : Finset Gen, span genRed (fun y => y ‚ąą H) conserv ‚ÜĒ conserv ‚ąą H) := by
  refine ‚ü®?_, ?_, ?_, ?_, ?_‚ü©
  ¬∑ -- (i) normalisation generated by the conservation generator (R6_Agent6).
    exact cw_sum p_X h_norm parts h_disjoint h_cover
  ¬∑ -- (i) the floor on the conserved mixture (R6_Agent6 = R5_Agent8 ‚ąė R5_Agent1).
    rw [charge_value_is_conservation_only]
    exact conserved_mixture_fano_floor p_X h_norm parts h_disjoint h_cover
      N logCardM Phi0 cardMmax hN_nonneg hcap_nonneg hcardMmax hcap_le hfano
  ¬∑ -- (ii) axis-localization: charge = conservation-only mixture.
    exact charge_value_is_conservation_only p_X N
  ¬∑ -- (iii) necessity (R6_Agent1 span = membership).
    exact fisher_scaling_misses_conserv
  ¬∑ -- (iv) characterization (R6_Agent1 span = membership).
    exact conserv_spanned_iff_mem

